meanings.definition: Not able to be attributed or credited to a particular source.
meanings.sent1: The mysterious painting was unattributable to any known artist.
meanings.sent2: The anonymous letter was unattributable to any specific sender.
meanings.sent3: The unattributable note left us all guessing who the secret admirer could be.
meanings.sent4: Her unattributable talent for music seemed to come from another world.
meanings.sent5: The unattributable scent in the room made everyone curious about its origin.

meanings.definition: Not attributable; not capable of being attributed.
meanings.sent1: The unattributable error in the report puzzled the team.
meanings.sent2: The unattributable noise in the night scared the children.
meanings.sent3: The unattributable glitch in the system caused chaos in the office.
meanings.sent4: His unattributable success in the competition surprised everyone.
meanings.sent5: The unattributable shadow in the corner made her uneasy.
